			 Matthew Bietz 
		 

				


					 
						
					 Matthew Bietz studies collaborative practices in, with, and around large-scale information infrastructures. He is an Assistant Project Scientist in Informatics at UCI and is also an Affiliate Assistant Professor in Human Centered Design and Engineering at the University of Washington. He holds a Ph.D. in Information from the University of Michigan.Matt draws on a diverse background, including information and library science, science, technology and society (STS), organizational behavior, historical musicology, cello performance, English literature, cultural studies, and feminist practice.
 As Associate Director of EVOKE, Matt is cultivating projects to explore how information infrastructures influence what we know and how we live. 
 


					 

				


				

			 
 

